formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1. In view of agreement to sale dated 10/02/2021 executed between the promoter and the land owners, the promoters have duly discharged their obligation to make full payments towards purchase of land to the land owners of Rs.16,90,00,000/-. In view of the said agreement the total estimated project cost figures at Rs.46,80,25,351/- instead of Rs. 43,31,33,199/-.
2. Total estimated cost has been revised by engineer subsequently at Rs. 27,97,50,000/- as can be verified from latest Form 2 issued by him. However, as informed by him and promoter of project, there are no utilities on GujRera website to make such changes/ revisions online and hence figure of estimated total cost as per engineer's certificate is being auto populated in Form 3 as per column No. 1 (ii) a(i) are still appearing at old estimates of engineer. 
3. Total estimated payments to statutory authority as per Sr. No. 1 (ii) (b) was revised at Rs. 29,82,152/- instead of Rs. 9,72,000/-. However, actual expense has been incurred to the tune of Rs. 42,29,427/- so far. 
4. Rs. 33,90,35,957/- stated against row 7 of above certificate being the amount withdrawn till date of this certificate as per books and bank statement includes the amount withdrawn from designated bank of Rs.29,08,30,125/- and non designated bank of Rs. 4,82,05,832/-.
5. Total actual cost incurred and paid for project and amount which can be withdrawn from designated account as per column no. 3 and 6 is Rs. 47,31,65,079/- instead of Rs. 40,95,75,389/- (as appearing above due to portal restrictions). Therefore, net amount which can be withdrawn from designated account as per column no. 8 would be 13,41,29,122/- instead of Rs. 7,05,39,432/-.
